This repository provides the official implementation of the paper:
USTGA: Unified Spatial-Temporal Graph Aggregation for Student Performance Prediction

This work proposes a **Unified Spatial-Temporal Graph Aggregation (USTGA)** framework for student performance prediction.  
Unlike conventional approaches that model spatial and temporal dependencies separately, USTGA integrates spatial similarity directly into temporal dependency modeling within a unified graph structure.
The model further employs:
- Attention-guided aggregation
- Multi-layer feature refinement
- Inductive neighborhood-based representation learning 
to effectively capture complex spatial-temporal interactions.
